.TH HSH 1 "7 September 2022" "1.0" "simple_shell man page"
.SH NAME
.B simple_shell
- Simple Shell for ALX School
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ./hsh
[command] [options]
.SH DESCRIPTION
(Simple Shell) is an end of first sprint project in ALX software engineering program, where we understand the  C programming language, which was used to build a simple shell program.

The shell command reads lines from either the terminal or a file, it interprets them, and executes the commands. The program runs until the user ends.


.B Overview

The simple shell is a simplified iteration of a command line interpreter similar to
.B bash or
.B dash.
.I FORMAT [ARGUMENT]...
.SH OPTIONS
.B Simple Shell
operates in both
.I interactive
and
.I non-interactive
mode. The user may initiate
.B simple shell
and begin working or initate
.B simple shell
using commands meant to be run by the program.
.SH ARGUMENTS
The first argument, argument 0 is understood to be the command to be run by
.B simple shell
and arguments following as modifier or options.
.SH Return value
The return value of a simple command is its exit status
.SH Example
.PP

$./hsh

$

$ls

